spanishExample: Después de casarnos, se nos ocurrió la mejor idea.
englishTranslation: After getting married, we came up with the best idea.

spanishExample: Si te casas, yo me caso.
englishTranslation: If you get married, I get married.

spanishExample: Nos habíamos casado antes del año ochenta y nueve porque nos amamos.
englishTranslation: We had gotten married before the year eighty-nine because we love each other.

spanishExample: Ella quiere que yo duerma antes de nuestra misión.
englishTranslation: She wants me to sleep before our mission.

spanishExample: Terminaré esta tarea para que ella duerma.
englishTranslation: I’ll finish this task so that she sleeps.

spanishExample: No quiero que se case, porque si se casa será malo para mí.
englishTranslation: I don’t want her to get married, because if she gets married it will be bad for me.

spanishExample: Te casaste hace ochenta horas y yo he estado durmiendo desde entonces.
englishTranslation: You got married eighty hours ago and I’ve been sleeping since then.

spanishExample: No duermo de la misma manera que tu duermes.
englishTranslation: I don’t sleep in the same manner that you sleep.

spanishExample: Lo he amado por noventa y un días.
englishTranslation: I have loved him for ninety-one days.

spanishExample: Se le ocurrirá algo para la boda.
englishTranslation: He will come up with something for the wedding.

spanishExample: ¡No te duermas! Voy a casarme en un par de horas.
englishTranslation: Don’t fall asleep! I’m going to get married in a couple of hours.

spanishExample: Esta es una pelea tonta, tú la amas.
englishTranslation: This is a silly fight, you love her.

spanishExample: Si se te ocurre una buena idea, por favor dime qué es.
englishTranslation: If you come up with a good idea, please tell me what it is.

spanishExample: No te puedes dormir durante la carrera.
englishTranslation: You can’t fall asleep during the race.

spanishExample: Quiero que duermas ahora para que no haya sorpresas después.
englishTranslation: I want you to sleep now so there aren't any surprises later.

spanishExample: Ella no te ama, pero yo te amo.
englishTranslation: She doesn’t love you, but I love you.

spanishExample: Escuchamos noventa y dos canciones, no ochenta y tres.
englishTranslation: We heard ninety-two songs, not eighty-three.

spanishExample: Se le ha ocurrido un buen proyecto, para su sorpresa.
englishTranslation: He has come up with a good project, to his surprise.

spanishExample: Se me está ocurriendo un buen plan para nuestro negocio.
englishTranslation: I’m coming up with a good plan for our business.

spanishExample: Siempre duerme durante nuestras reuniones.
englishTranslation: He always sleeps during our meetings.

spanishExample: Durmió en esa casa por noventa y nueve días.
englishTranslation: He slept in that house for ninety-nine days.

spanishExample: Cuando me case, voy a tener esa canción en mi boda porque me gusta la letra.
englishTranslation: When I get married, I’ll have that song at my wedding, because I like the lyrics.

spanishExample: Ella te amaba, pero tú no la amabas y por eso no se casaron.
englishTranslation: She loved you, but you didn’t love her and that’s why you didn’t marry each other.

spanishExample: Se aman y van a casarse el próximo mes.
englishTranslation: They love each other and they are going to get married next month.

spanishExample: Nos casamos en el año ochenta y ocho y fue un éxito.
englishTranslation: We got married in the year eighty-eight and it was a success.

spanishExample: Siempre se te ocurren las mejores ideas, esta es la número noventa y seis.
englishTranslation: You always come up with the best ideas, this is number ninety-six.

spanishExample: Tienes que casarte o sería un error.
englishTranslation: You have to get married or it would be a mistake.

spanishExample: No he dormido desde que ella se casó.
englishTranslation: I haven’t slept since she got married.

spanishExample: Ella te puede amar y luego ustedes se pueden casar.
englishTranslation: She can love you and then you can get married.

spanishExample: Lo amaba, entonces me casé con él.
englishTranslation: I loved him, so I married him.

spanishExample: Si nos casamos, cambiaré la primera letra de mi nombre.
englishTranslation: If we get married, I’ll change the first letter of my name.

spanishExample: Dormí mucho porque esa música me da calma.
englishTranslation: I slept a lot because that music gives me calm.
